<section class="content-spacing grid-container" id="type-shostakovich">
    <div>
        <h2 class="sub-text">Dimitri Shostakovich Composition Poster</h2>

        <h3 class="description-text">Dimitri Shostakovich composed Symphony No. 5 in D Minor, Opus 47 in July of 1937. This piece is a reposed to just criticism and it follows the journey of the society until the finale which is a satirical picture of a dictator. This piece is in the colors of the soviets posters during that period. In addition, some elements follow the structure of the Soviets posters such as the type lockups, shapes, and emphasis. Shostakovich’s name is hiding behind the 5 to resemble his constant struggle with the Soviet government and how he would hide behind his music. Click the image below to see the process sketches of the poster.</h3>

