<section class="content-spacing grid-container" id="type-caslon">
    <div>
        <h2 class="sub-text">Caslon Type Speciman</h2>

        <h3 class="description-text">Caslon is a typeface that was created by William Caslon in 1722. He used influences from Dutch baroque fonts and British Georgian architecture during the time. Caslon was a gunlock and barrel engraver before making his way into type. I wanted to incorporate this when creating the design and type lockups. Before creating Caslon, William designed an English Arabic typeface which had a large influence on his typeface Caslon, especially in the serifs. I tried to mimic elements of this with the connection of the R and the T that look as if they could create a new letterform. </h3>

